div.p: From William Lamb Smith to the Executors of the Mueller Estate
No. 62/802, unit 802, VPRS 28 Probate and Administration Files, VA 2624, Public Record Office, Victoria.

The valuation forms part of the bundle of papers related to the grant of probate of M's will dated 17 June 1884 (in this edition as 84-06-17). The papers include affidavits concerning James Rudall's renouncing the role of executor and the remaining executors (Alexander Büttner, Hermann Büttner and William Potter) swearing to the accuracy of the accounts; John George Luehmann and Charles French each swearing to the authenticity of the will and that the alterations in it were made before they signed as witnesses; a summary of M's assets and liabilities at death (see A. Büttner et al. to Supreme Court of Victoria, 12 November 1896 (in this edition as M96-11-12)); a statement of the executors' account in 1900 (see A. Büttner et al. to Supreme Court, 28 June 1900 (in this edition as M1900-06-28)); and the formal grant of probate, dated 16 November 1896. Valuation of Household Furniture, Effects Books Jewellery &c
In the Estate of the late Baron Ferdinand J. H. Von Mueller
